37 SECTION 7.(a) Article 9A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by
38 adding the following new sections to read:
39 "§ 90-171.36B. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure.
40 (a) No advanced practice registered nurse shall practice as an advanced practice
41 registered nurse unless the nurse is licensed by the Board under this section.
42 (b) An applicant for a license to practice as an APRN shall apply to the Board in a format
43 prescribed by the Board and pay a fee in an amount determined under G.S. 90-171.27.
44 (c) The Board shall adopt rules, not inconsistent with this Article, which identify the
45 criteria which must be met by an applicant in order to be issued a license.
46 "§ 90-171.36C. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure; grandfathering exceptions.
47 (a) The Board shall issue an APRN license to any person recognized by the Board as an
48 APRN or approved to practice as an APRN in this State on or before the date that this section
49 becomes law.
50 (b) An advanced practice registered nurse licensed under this section shall maintain all
51 practice privileges provided to licensed advanced practice registered nurses under this Chapter.
Page 6 DRS35424-NBf-182

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 90-171.36D. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure renewal; reinstatement.
2 (a) An applicant for renewal of an APRN license issued under this Article shall apply for
3 licensure renewal according to the frequency and schedule established by the Board and pay the
4 required fee.
5 (b) Failure to renew the APRN license before the expiration date shall result in automatic
6 forfeiture of the right to practice nursing as an APRN in North Carolina until such time as the
7 license has been reinstated.
8 (c) An APRN licensee who has allowed his or her license to lapse by failure to renew
9 may apply for reinstatement in a manner prescribed by the Board and pay the required fee.
10 (d) The Board shall adopt rules, not inconsistent with this Article, which identify the
11 criteria which must be met by an applicant for APRN license renewal or reinstatement."
